  "body": "\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-eb36bbb83e009b9d1541a49cb4cc779e wp-block-paragraph\">Steps to set up, edit, and manage client quotations in the CRM — adding sections and items, setting tax type, tracking quotation status, downloading and sharing with clients, and using the rate library for faster item entry.</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-53099\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"448\" src=\"/images/recon/Add-a-heading-42-1024x448.webp\" width=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-0c48903c91055c77db159d77e794652a\">\n<li>The client must be added as a party before they can be selected on a quotation</li>\n<li>Add items to the Rate Library in advance for faster quotation creation</li>\n<li>Configure Terms and Conditions in Settings if you want default terms to pre-fill on quotations</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accessing Quotations</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-e0f73ba8f6b940eec4ec9e9ba8ae7115 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>CRM</strong> in the left sidebar, then click the <strong>Quotation</strong> tab.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-d761e546e39b3b7869851100c6373db2 wp-block-paragraph\">Quotations can also be created from within a lead: open the lead, click the <strong>Quotation</strong> tab, and click <strong>+ New Quotation</strong>. This links the quotation to the lead automatically.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Quotation List</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>S.No</td><td>Auto-generated quotation number (e.g. QT 2025/23)</td></tr><tr><td>Date</td><td>Date the quotation was created</td></tr><tr><td>Subject</td><td>Quotation title</td></tr><tr><td>Client</td><td>Client name</td></tr><tr><td>Est. Amount</td><td>Total estimated value in Rs</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>Current quotation stage</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Filters</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Filter</th><th>Options</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Search</td><td>Search by quotation subject or client name</td></tr><tr><td>Date Filter</td><td>Filter by date range</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>All, Draft, Sent, In Discussion, On Hold, Client Confirmed, Rejected</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Quotation Status Values</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>What It Means</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Draft</strong></td><td>Being prepared, not yet shared with the client</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Sent</strong></td><td>Shared with the client</td></tr><tr><td><strong>In Discussion</strong></td><td>Client is reviewing or negotiating</td></tr><tr><td><strong>On Hold</strong></td><td>Paused — waiting on client or internal decision</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Client Confirmed</strong></td><td>Client has approved the quotation</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Rejected</strong></td><td>Client declined</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-f3fba2da0ba59afec738db3a76e20dd7 wp-block-paragraph\">Update the status directly from the list by clicking the status badge on any row.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Creating a New Quotation</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6193c7ebca5ab0b5a2e3f0873bf8d6fc wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>+ New Quotation</strong> in the top right.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create Quotation Form</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Required</th><th>What to Enter</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Quotation Subject</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Descriptive title (e.g. “Full Home Interior — Sector 22”)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Client Name</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Search and select from existing parties</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Select Tax Type</strong></td><td>Yes</td><td>Item Level Tax (tax per line item) or Bill Level Tax (single tax applied to the total)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow\">\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-e489898d6986757a6481dac8c7a3dbf6 wp-block-paragraph\">⚠️ Tax Type cannot be changed after the quotation is saved. Choose carefully before clicking Save. Item Level Tax is used when different items attract different GST rates. Bill Level Tax is used when a single rate applies to the entire quotation.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6706d79c9ca67a2651da755526dd82dd wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>Save Quotation</strong>. The quotation opens in edit mode.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Quotation Detail View</h2>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Header Fields</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>What It Shows or Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>QT No.</td><td>Auto-generated reference (e.g. Qt 2025/23)</td></tr><tr><td>QT Date</td><td>Date of the quotation</td></tr><tr><td>Client</td><td>Client name</td></tr><tr><td>GST</td><td>Client’s GST number (auto-filled from party profile)</td></tr><tr><td>Mobile</td><td>Client’s phone number</td></tr><tr><td>Address</td><td>Client’s address</td></tr><tr><td>Status</td><td>Current stage — change via dropdown</td></tr><tr><td>Priority</td><td>High, Medium, or Low</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Action Buttons</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Button</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Download</strong></td><td>Export the quotation as a PDF or file</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Edit</strong></td><td>Enter edit mode to update items, prices, or details</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Print</strong></td><td>Print the quotation directly</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Share</strong></td><td>Share the quotation with the client via WhatsApp or email</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding Sections and Items</h2>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Add a Section</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-739f0eb3953b2dbf615519263021c4d4 wp-block-paragraph\">Click <strong>+ Section</strong> to create a grouping row (e.g. “Civil Work”, “Electrical”, “Plumbing”, “Interior Finishes”). Items added below a section become sub-items (2.1, 2.2, etc.) under that section heading.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-23741cd483db594a2c430b36027797b2 wp-block-paragraph\">Use sections to organise large quotations by trade or scope. Clients find sectioned quotations significantly easier to read and approve.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Add an Item</h3>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-24bf0b3bff6a7aac66d9bce87f9d415e wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Option A — From Library:</strong> Click <strong>+ Add Item</strong>, then <strong>+ Add Item from Library</strong>. Search and select a predefined item. All fields pre-fill from the library entry.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-dd9eae610b228a0b13a589c593225307 wp-block-paragraph\"><strong>Option B — New Item (manual):</strong> Click <strong>+ Add Item</strong> and enter all fields manually.</p>\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Items Table Fields</h3>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>What to Enter</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Item</td><td>Item name or description</td></tr><tr><td>N x L x W x H</td><td>Dimensions (for area or volume-based items, e.g. flooring in sqft, concrete in cum)</td></tr><tr><td>Cost Price</td><td>Your internal cost for this item in Rs</td></tr><tr><td>Selling Price</td><td>Price charged to the client in Rs</td></tr><tr><td>QTY</td><td>Quantity with unit (e.g. 100 sqft, 5 points, 12 nos)</td></tr><tr><td>Tax (%)</td><td>Tax rate for this item (e.g. 18%, 12%, 5%)</td></tr><tr><td>Amount</td><td>Auto-calculated as Selling Price multiplied by QTY, adjusted for tax</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-8a5ec27c18ee915a930b65c66c084844 wp-block-paragraph\">Click the <strong>three dots (⋮)</strong> on any item row to Edit or Delete that item. Collapse or expand sections using the arrow icon on the section row.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Financial Summary</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Item Sub Total</strong></td><td>Sum of all item amounts before tax adjustment</td></tr><tr><td><strong>CGST</strong></td><td>Central GST portion (typically 9%)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>SGST</strong></td><td>State GST portion (typically 9%)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Additional Discount</strong></td><td>Manual discount applied to the total in Rs</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total Amount</strong></td><td>Final amount after tax and discount</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cost Price</strong></td><td>Total internal cost to your company across all items</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Markup</strong></td><td>Total Amount minus Cost Price — your profit on this quotation</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-1745c23399e7da285259bce41a18ae08 wp-block-paragraph\">Review the Markup before sharing with the client. If the Cost Price and Selling Price were set correctly on each item, the Markup shows your net margin for the full quotation scope.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Terms and Conditions</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-6f8840c64c0da1cf976ce56697dc5b1b wp-block-paragraph\">A Terms and Conditions section appears at the bottom of the quotation. Edit the text to reflect your payment terms, change request policy, validity period, or any contractual notes specific to this quotation.</p>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-8435c56cb93efe931d06e73524b9c517 wp-block-paragraph\">Default terms from Settings are pre-filled if configured. See Steps to Include Terms and Conditions for setup guidance.</p>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Duplicate or Delete a Quotation</h2>\n<p class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-38475c75153c35c7c76c0407f380109d wp-block-paragraph\">Click the <strong>three dots (⋮)</strong> on any quotation row in the list:</p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>What It Does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Duplicate</strong></td><td>Creates an identical copy of the quotation — useful for similar projects where only prices or quantities differ</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Delete</strong></td><td>Permanently removes the quotation</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips</h2>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-25aac924350ab435d148f383509d073e\">\n<li>Use Sections to organise by trade. A quotation with sections for Civil, Electrical, Plumbing, and Interior is much easier for a client to review than a flat list of 40 items.</li>\n<li>Set Tax Type before saving. Item Level Tax applies different rates per item — use it for mixed-trade quotations. Bill Level Tax applies one rate to the total — use it for single-scope work.</li>\n<li>Add items from the Rate Library for consistency and speed. Library items carry pre-set cost and selling prices, so you only need to enter the quantity.</li>\n<li>Check the Markup before sharing. The financial summary shows total Cost Price and Markup. Send the quotation only when the margin is within your target.</li>\n<li>Move status to Client Confirmed once approved. This makes it easy to filter all confirmed quotations and convert them to projects.</li>\n<li>Create quotations from within the lead record, not from the Quotations tab directly, whenever possible. This keeps the lead and quotation linked for pipeline tracking.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">If Something Goes Wrong</h2>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-palette-color-4-color has-text-color has-link-color has-border-color has-palette-color-1-border-color has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-width:2px\"><thead><tr><th>Problem</th><th>Likely Cause</th><th>What to Do</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Client not appearing in the dropdown</td><td>Not added as a party</td><td>Add the client as a party first, then create the quotation</td></tr><tr><td>Tax not calculating</td><td>Tax percentage not entered on items, or Tax Type not set</td><td>Check the Tax (%) column on each item and confirm the Tax Type was selected at creation</td></tr><tr><td>Item not in Library</td><td>Not yet added</td><td>Add the item manually in this quotation, or ask Admin to add it to the Rate Library</td></tr><tr><td>Quotation not visible in list</td><td>Status filter is active</td><td>Set the Status filter to All</td></tr><tr><td>Cannot change Tax Type after saving</td><td>Tax Type is locked after save</td><td>Delete the quotation and recreate it with the correct Tax Type selected</td></tr><tr><td>Markup showing zero or negative</td><td>Selling Price set equal to or below Cost Price</td><td>Review each item’s Cost Price and Selling Price and correct the margins</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n"
}